MEMBERS of an extraordinary meeting of the Chama Cha Mapinduzi (CCM)’s general congress have unanimously endorsed Mr Abdulrahman Kinana as the party’s new Vice Chairperson for Mainland. Mr Kinana garnered all 1875 valid votes cast at the extraordinary meeting of the general congress chaired by national chairperson, Samia Suluhu Hassan. Yesterday, the National Executive Committee (NEC) nominated Mr. Abdulrahman Kinana to run for the position of Vice-Chairman CCM-Mainland following the incumbent Elder, Philip Mangula's decision to resign voluntarily. Speaking shortly after the election, Mr Kinana thanked CCM Chairperson and promised to discharge their duties diligently to strengthen the party. Also Read: Why Kinana? “For a party to be strong, democracy within the party must be strong…for democracy to prosper, we must uphold justice,” said the newly elected party’s Vice Chairman for Mainland. The veteran politician emphasized on justice within the party, stating that it must be practiced within the party. “If we can strengthen justice within the CCM we will be able to strengthen justice outside CCM,” he added. 